title: Power Outage Predictor
description:
A machine learning model that predicts large-scale power outages using historical U.S. data. 
                Built with Random Forest and includes data on weather, land use, and energy consumption.

title: Language Models and Text
description: Built and fine-tuned a basic large language model to generate text completions based on user input, experimenting with tokenization and word embeddings.

title: Loan Application Analysis
description: Conducted a predictive analysis on loan application data to identify key factors influencing loan approvals using logistic regression and decision trees.

title: MTS Transit Data Analysis
description: Analyzed San Diego MTS public transit data to uncover ridership patterns, delays, and system usage trends through data cleaning, visualization, and mapping.

title: Superhero Sequel Predictor
description: Designed a Random Forest model to predict whether a superhero movie sequels based on superhero characteristics. The model achieved an accuracy of 85% on the test set.
